name: prime95

variants.name: build_system
variants.description: Build systems supported by the package

description:
Prime95, also distributed as the command-line utility mprime for
FreeBSD and Linux, is a freeware application. Prime95 is a CPU stress
testing program. It tests your computer for stability issues by
stressing your CPU to its maximum limit. Prime95 runs indefinitely and
only terminates a stress test when it encounters an error and informs
the user that the system may be unstable.
